  "texts": [
    "In AI-focused tasks, saliency maps were more helpful when the AI was incorrect.",
    "At first glance, there seems to be a paradox regarding AI accuracy.",
    "On the one hand, it was suggested that saliency maps help people understand that the AI may err (Yang et al., 2021).",
    "On the other hand, it was observed that they do not help them understand why (Colin et al., 2022; Fel et al., 2023; Shen & Huang, 2020).",
    "More specifically, the understanding of failure cases (i.e., frequently confused classes) was not supported."
